Reasoning: The paper discusses the construction of succinct automata based on different algebraic structures, which is a topic that falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory. The paper also mentions the use of Eilenberg-Moore algebras, which is a concept from category theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Other likely sub-categories include cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science).
